        p(data-bottom-top="transform: translateY(-50px);opacity: 0" data-center="transform: translateY(0px);opacity: 1") The red-wine production process involves extraction of color and flavor components from the grape skin. Red wine is made from dark-colored grape varieties. The actual color of the wine can range from violet, typical of young wines, through red for mature wines, to brown for older red wines.       
      .col-md-4.col-sm-6
